    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stricter Sentences for Serious Offenders and Improved Community Safety",
        "additional_details": "Current penalties often seem to fail to deter offenders or adequately protect communities, leaving residents feeling unsafe and victims\u2019 families without sufficient justice.\r\n\r\n1. Impose stricter prison sentences for serious crimes, including repeat offenders.\r\n2. Increase funding and resources for crime prevention, community safety programs, and rehabilitation initiatives.\r\n3. Provide better support for victims of crime and their families, ensuring timely and transparent legal processes.\r\n \r\nThese measures will help protect communities, reduce repeat offenses, and restore public confidence in the justice system.\r\n",
        "background": "In recent years, there have been reports that serious crimes, including violent assaults and murders, have been increasing across the UK. ",
